Barloworld, Kumba, MTN and Nedbank Could Move: South Africa Equity Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-05-05T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/barloworld-kumba-mtn-group-nedbank-s-african-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parenthesis and prices are from
the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index fell 274.50, or 0.9
percent, to 31,582.14 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg, the
lowest since April 18.  Barloworld Ltd. (BAW)  : The world’s largest forklift
trader said it expects earnings excluding one-time items from
continuing operations to be between 1.30 and 1.56 rand in the
first half through March, compared to 41 cents a year earlier,
according to a regulatory statement. The stock lost 45 cents, or
0.6 percent, to 73.05 rand.  Cadiz Holdings Ltd. (CDZ)  : The financial services
holding company said it expects its earnings to decline by as
much as 44 percent a share in the year through March compared
with a year earlier, according to a regulatory statement. Cadiz
was unchanged at 2.70 rand.  Kumba Iron Ore Ltd. (KIO)  : The producer of the steel-
making ingredient holds a shareholders’ meeting. Kumba advanced
1.01 rand, or 0.2 percent, to 449.50 rand.  MTN Group Ltd. (MTN)  : Africa’s biggest mobile-network
operator publishes subscriber numbers for the first quarter. MTN
gained 51 cents, 0.4 percent, to 143.40 rand.  Nedbank Group Ltd. (NED)  : South Africa’s fourth-biggest
lender releases a trading update for the first quarter and also
holds an annual meeting of shareholders. Nedbank slipped 1.75
rand, or 1.2 percent, to 140.90 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
 smantshantsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
